article.headline: Georgia rallies from six-point deficit
article.story:
STARKVILLE, Miss. (AP) -- Tasha Humphey had 24 points and 12 rebounds, helping No. 21 Georgia rally past Mississippi State 67-57 on Sunday.

Sherill Baker finished with 14 points and Megan Darrah added 10 for Georgia (15-5, 4-2 Southeastern Conference), which rallied from a six-point halftime deficit.

Tan White led Mississippi State (14-4, 3-2 SEC) with 22 points. Rebecca Kates added 15 and Tiania Burns scored 11.

Georgia shot 44.1 percent from the floor and held Mississippi State to 36.4 percent shooting.
